Obviously not. The monster just roared and tried to charge directly at Sasalin. Thank goodness, although Sasalin was huge, he was still quite agile and managed to dodge in time. However, Nishi couldn't help but scream and almost slipped off Sasalin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill them?" Nishi shouted.
"Aim for their heads!"
"This is too hard!"
Sasalin roared, circled around, and flew toward the mountain he called home. The black monster followed closely, but when attacked from behind by fire, it became somewhat panicked. The monster had not yet realized it had gained another opponent. Sasalin slowed down and then struck the monster's head forcefully with his tail, knocking it off course. The monster became even more panicked.
The monster roared, emitting a hissing sound from its throat, flying straight upward while continuously spitting something into the air. Suddenly, everything around became pitch black, as if the monster were absorbing the light from the sky and replacing it with an eternal night.
Sasalin's vision went black for a moment, and he tried to step back, but found himself colliding with the treetops and falling onto the ground below. It seemed that the monster clearly knew where Sasalin had fallen, flying straight toward him, taking the mass of clouds with it.
"Kayer!" Tenuk shouted, flying out of the clouds, beginning to circle around, trying to find Nisi and Sasalin in the darkness below. "What should we do, Kayer...? Kayer, where are you?"
Nisi struggled to stand up. She felt certain she had broken some bones, but her strange, unnatural self-healing ability had already begun to take effect. Sasalin's situation was different; he was lying helplessly on the ground, leaning against a tree that he had crushed. Nisi tried to walk toward Sasalin, but she could barely see anything due to the darkness. Terrible shadows surrounded her, and something was screaming within the shadows.
A terrible club-like tail smashed down violently onto the ground, knocking Nisi off her feet. She noticed that the tail was flailing wildly, but it seemed its target was not her. Nisi barely saw the monster roaring and frantically scratching at the shadows it had created with its claws. Something was teleporting within the darkness, waiting for an opportunity to strike the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot shattered the air, and the monster immediately fell silent, collapsing motionless on the ground. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth. Kayel stood on the monster's corpse, holding a rifle, panting heavily.
"That was... one of the strangest shadow jumps I've ever done... Tanto Katelorn..." Kayel panted. For some reason, his eyes glowed with a dark light, and a surge of dark energy flowed within him. However, just as Kayel began to speak, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
After a while, Nishi finally understood what had happened. They all knew that Kayel possessed a strange shadow ability, but he rarely used this power, as most people believed it to be extremely evil and terrifying. However, Nishi didn't know that Kayel could use this ability in any darkness. Moreover, from Kayel's expression, it was clear that he himself was also very surprised.
"Are you okay?" Nishi couldn't help but ask.
"I'm fine. I killed that thing, and I'll be back to normal soon." Kayel looked at his "masterpiece," and at that moment, Trenuk landed beside him, transforming back into his original Spast形态.
Now, the monster was no longer moving, and they could take a good look at what it actually was. Its skin was dark and shiny, covered with a sticky liquid that clung tightly to the monster's body. It had four wings and four legs, each ending in long, slender claws, and two straight horns grew from its skull.
Tenook and Kayer hadn't even had time to ask what the hell this thing was when another monster screamed and leaped out from the nearby bushes. At that moment, a familiar car crashed into the side of the monster, sending it sliding a short distance before coming to a stop at Nishi's feet. Without hesitation, Nishi grabbed the shotgun and fired directly at the monster's head, killing it instantly.
"Ouch..." Retwick muttered from the driver's seat, then awkwardly turned off the engine and climbed down from the truck. "Uh, that wasn't intentional. Are you all okay?"
"You missed all the fun!" Tenook said, grumbling. "Where did you disappear to?"
"You left me behind," Retwick sighed. "I did my best to catch up... Please, what are these terrible things?"
Retvik's question was answered by Sasalin, who had already risen. He was covered in wounds and scratches, looking a bit dazed, but his injuries did not seem serious.
"You killed the Corrupted! Those infected monsters. When the Corruption attacked your god, these creatures were left here."
"You mean... we... helped kill the terrible monster god?" Tenruk stuttered a bit.
"Yes, that's right. There might be more Corrupted. But I can't shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun. And two against one isn't fair, is it?" Sasalin walked up to Kayel and patted his head. "Thank you, little one. You remind me of my old friend Arkadin. Just you aren't as ruthless as him, nor do you have his ability to destroy the universe."
"Uh... thank you... I think..." Kayel shrugged. "So, uh, did we complete the mission?"
Nix shrugged her shoulders, picked up the camera, and took several pictures of those monsters that were definitely dead. Then, she pulled out her favorite dagger—the exquisite Death Scythe—and began cutting off one of the monster's horns, then the other. However, the moment Nix finished cutting, the monsters suddenly began to combust, quickly turning into a pile of ashes. The horns Nix had cut off also turned to ashes.
"Well... this is a mixed blessing..." Nix sighed. "At least I still have the photos, right?"
